<div class="case-story__chapter case-story__chapter--lightGrey">
  <h2>Initial assessment</h2>
  <p>Common with first iteration MVPs, the user interface had been assembled on-the-fly as features were developed. Once the core functionality had been proven, it was time to refactor those decisions into something efficient and easy-to-use.</p>
  <p>There was a lot of room to consolidate and prioritize. Two separate lists of alerts existed, which were performing the same duty &mdash; just in different ways. Information, overall, was flat with no emphasis assigned to important content.</p>
